`,o.jsx(n.li,{children:"Vickrey (second-price sealed bid): Truthful bidding incentives; winner pays second-highest."}),`
`,o.jsx(n.li,{children:"Reverse (buyer-driven): Treasury posts desired price; sellers compete to fill at discounts."}),`
`]}),`
`,o.jsx(n.h3,{children:"Ensuring Lender Safety and Enforcement in CRDT Loans"}),`
`,o.jsx(n.p,{children:"This section expands on Whitepaper Sections 5–6 (Collateral Valuation, Loan Lifecycle, and Enforcement). The goal is a binding, on-chain system where lenders are protected by conservative math and automatic settlement, without relying on off-chain trust."}),`
`,o.jsx(n.h4,{children:"1. Protocol Control of Vested Tokens (No Swap/Sell Until Settled)"}),`
`,o.jsxs(n.ul,{children:[`
`,o.jsx(n.li,{children:"Escrow of claim rights (not tokens): When a borrower takes a loan, they escrow claim rights via a vesting adapter. The underlying tokens remain locked in the original vesting contract until the unlock timestamp."}),`
`,o.jsx(n.li,{children:"Non-transferability during vesting: Standard vesting contracts enforce that tokens cannot be transferred before unlock."}),`
`,o.jsx(n.li,{children:"At unlock: The protocol intercepts release. The loan contract checks outstanding debt before tokens are released."}),`
`,o.jsxs(n.li,{children:["Permissionless settlement: Once ",o.jsx(n.code,{children:"block.timestamp >= unlockTime"}),", anyone can call ",o.jsx(n.code,{children:"settleAtUnlock(loanId)"}),"."]}),`
`,o.jsxs(n.li,{children:["Enforcement outcomes:",`
`,o.jsxs(n.ul,{children:[`
`,o.jsx(n.li,{children:"Full repay: Tokens are released to the borrower."}),`
`,o.jsx(n.li,{children:"Partial repay: The protocol seizes only the amount needed to cover remaining debt + interest and returns the excess."}),`
`,o.jsx(n.li,{children:"Default: The protocol seizes the full unlocked amount for liquidation to repay lenders."}),`
`]}),`
`]}),`
`]}),`
`,o.jsx(n.h4,{children:"2. Lender Safety Mechanisms"}),`
`,o.jsxs(n.ul,{children:[`
`,o.jsx(n.li,{children:"Conservative DPV and LTV caps: Discounted present value applies time, volatility, liquidity, unlock impact, and protocol risk factors. LTV is capped (20–40% in the litepaper, adjustable by governance)."}),`
`,o.jsx(n.li,{children:"Interest accrual: Interest compounds in the loan manager and is added to the repayment amount at settlement."}),`
`,o.jsx(n.li,{children:"Liquidation on default: Seized tokens are liquidated via DEX/OTC routes to repay lenders in stablecoins."}),`
`,o.jsx(n.li,{children:"Governance controls: High-volatility tokens can receive lower LTV, higher discounts, or temporary pauses."}),`
`,o.jsx(n.li,{children:"Cross-chain reputation: Defaults can reduce credit terms on other supported chains."}),`
`]}),`
`,o.jsx(n.h4,{children:"3. Scenario Coverage (Up, Down, Default)"}),`
`,o.jsx(n.p,{children:"Example: 50,000 tokens at $1 today, 12-month vesting, 10% APR."}),`
`,o.jsxs(n.ul,{children:[`
`,o.jsxs(n.li,{children:["DPV example: ",o.jsx(n.code,{children:"PV = Q * P * D"})," with a conservative discount (e.g., 0.407) gives ~$20,350."]}),`
`,o.jsx(n.li,{children:"Max borrow at 30% LTV: ~$6,105; debt at unlock with interest: ~$6,715."}),`
`]}),`
`,o.jsx(n.p,{children:"Outcomes at unlock:"}),`
`,o.jsxs(n.ul,{children:[`
`,o.jsx(n.li,{children:"Price up ($5): Full repay releases tokens; partial repay seizes only the amount needed; default seizes all tokens and repays lenders with surplus."}),`
`,o.jsx(n.li,{children:"Price down ($0.50): Full repay releases tokens; partial/default seizes enough tokens to cover debt; discounts are set to withstand major drops."}),`
`,o.jsx(n.li,{children:"Extreme tail risk: If price collapses beyond the modeled discount, governance can pause or reprice the asset class."}),`
`]}),`
